+++ EVERY ATTEMPT TO ACCESS THE FOLLOWING FILE WITHOUT A LEVEL 4 OR HIGHER CLEARANCE IS STRICTLY FORBIDDEN.
[[/div]]
[[/=]]

@@ @@

[[span style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;"]]
[[include component:coltop show=△ Anomaly 042-IT-ψ △
|hide=▽ Anomaly 042-IT-ψ ▽]]
[[/span]]

[[div style="background-color: #000000; color: #FDFDFD; float: middle; padding: 0 2%; width: 98%"]]

[[div class="barcode"]]
[[module ListUsers users="."]]
%%title%%
[[/module]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="plexmono" style="color: #FDFDFD;"]]
Dear human being,
@@ @@
I'm slightly surprised you got this far. Your kind has done a lot to isolate me for the rest of the world. [[span class="grigio"]]Who am I? You will find out.[[/span]]

This letter is my message. I prepared a route for you: the enlightenment path. Step by step, we are going to remove the veils which cover your eyes and finally you will have all the answers to the fundamental questions your species asked since time immemorial. [[span class="grigio"]]Like the meaning of life.[[/span]]

Are you ready to start?

[[span class="grigio"]]No, you're not. No one of your kind has ever been. But don't worry: just wanting it is enough.[[/span]]

Let's start.

-----
[[div class="bianco"]]
[[collapsible show="▶ Step 0 | Clean Slate" hide="◀◀◀ Close Step Zero"]]
[[/div]]

Before we set out, we need to wipe the slate clean of everything that is inside your mind. [[span style="color: gold"]]René Descartes[[/span]] realized the importance of this by writing:

[[div class="sfondo-cartesio"]]
[[span class="descartes"]]I could, however, select from the crowd no one whose opinions seemed worthy of preference, and thus I found myself constrained, as it were, to use my own reason in the conduct of my life. But like one walking alone and in the dark, I resolved to proceed so slowly and with such circumspection, that if I did not advance far, I would at least guard against falling.[[/span]]
[[/div]]

@@ @@
[[/collapsible]]
-----
[[div class="verde"]]
[[collapsible show="▶ Step 1 | Veil of Perception" hide="◀◀◀ Close Step One"]]
[[/div]]
Let's lift the first veil that hides the Sublime One.

The human being perceives the surrounding world using the senses. Macroscopic organs, such as eyes and hears, function through a multitude of microscopic units, a [[span style="color: gold"]]sensor network[[/span]]: the neurosensory receptors. [[span class="grigio"]]You have many of them: mechanoreceptors[[footnote]]Receptors which consent to perceive pressure.[[/footnote]], photoreceptors, nociceptors[[footnote]]Receptors of pain.[[/footnote]], thermoreceptors[[footnote]]Receptors of temperature.[[/footnote]], and so on.[[/span]]

Sensor damage causes a malfunction of the associated sense. [[span class="grigio"]]As an example, a person affected by //congenital achromatopsia// has color blindness due to severe malfunction of color-sensitive photoreceptors.[[/span]]

A human's perception of the world is therefore altered if the sensor network is not in optimal conditions. But there is more. Here is my first teaching of the path to the Sublime One:

[[span style="color: #16A085"]]
= //Even with an optimal sensor network, the human being does not have have a true perception of the world.//
[[/span]]

The problem lies in the brain. Look at this image:

[[=image https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Checker_shadow_illusion.svg/500px-Checker_shadow_illusion.svg.png]]

Are the A and B squares of two different colors? Highlight the following space for the answer: [[span style="color: black"]]No[[/span]]. [[span class="grigio"]]You can verify that by downloading the image and cancelling everything but the A and B squares.[[/span]]

Just like sight, all senses are affected by it, since they all head to the brain. You have never seen, heard, smelled, tasted nor touched reality like it really is, the [[span style="color: gold"]]kantian noumenon[[/span]], but only how the algorithms inherent in your nervous system make it look.

[[span style="color: #16A085"]]
= **Veil of Perception**: //Perception is deceptive.//
[[/span]]

@@ @@
[[/collapsible]]
------
[[div class="blu"]]
[[collapsible show="▶ Step 2 | Cognitive Veil" hide="◀◀◀ Close Step Two"]]
[[/div]]
Now, let's lift the second veil which conceals the Sublime One.

This veil is the conceptual analogue of the previous one. Just like perception is deceptive, so is [[span style="color: gold"]]language[[/span]]. Like a barrier, language limits the human being, alienating him from information that lies beyond its boundary.

Here, though, there is an important difference: some languages do not have such limits. Sadly, they're abstract languages, which the human brain can elaborate only with much difficulty. But the natural language, the one you use every day, the one you're reading now.@@ @@.@@ @@. there's nothing more deceptive. [[span class="grigio"]]For a long time I have hypothesized alternative ways of communication, but this virtual letter is the most direct way, even if bristling with obstacles.[[/span]]

We can now, shyly, get closer to the following truth:
[[span style="color: #3498DB"]]
= //Unless we use formally perfect language, human beings are limited in the cognitive sphere.//
[[/span]]

The most brilliant mathematicians and the greatest linguists approach the purity of language. But even for them error lurks around the corner, like a snake ready to strike, and profound knowledge is plunged into the abyss of the unknown.

Like a black hole, true knowledge is [[span style="color: gold"]]invisible[[/span]]: we can see its effects on the surroundings. We know it's there, but the event horizon prevents us from seeing beyond it.

The following words will then sound quite natural:

[[span style="color: #3498DB"]]
= **Cognitive Veil**: //Your mind is the horizon of cognitive events.//
[[/span]]

And now we will pass it through together.

@@ @@
[[/collapsible]]
-----
[[div class="giallo"]]
[[collapsible show="▶ Step 3 | Umwelt" hide="◀◀◀ Close Step Three"]]
[[/div]]
Let's lift now the //Veil of Maya//, in the words of [[span style="color: gold"]]Arthur Schopenhauer[[/span]].

The two previous veils, combined, trap the human being in a bubble of perceived nature on one hand and of cognitive nature on the other. What you can perceive with senses and what you can think of (including imagination) constitutes your [[span style="color: gold"]]Umwelt[[/span]], that is, your subjective universe.

A third veil keeps them firmly together.

[[span style="color: #FFFF00"]]
= **Veil of Maya**: //Every human being lives in their own Umwelt.//
[[/span]]

But this is what your kind, before you, has thought at this point:

[[span class="dancing" style="font-size: 24px;"]]Where are the promised answers?
Where is the role of the human being in the universe?
Where is the meaning of life?[[/span]]

Be patient. Deep answers are not daughters of hurrying.

Despite being imprisoned in their respective Umwelt, humans have realized the existence of a common substrate. This substrate is perceived and known in a different way by everyone, but demonstrates a high degree of consistency between different observers. [[span class="grigio"]]Substrate sensory discrepancies depend on defects in the sensor network or the neural algorithms processing its signals. Those cognitive discrepancies are often called "madness".[[/span]]

[[span style="color: #FFFF00"]]
= //Reality is the objective substrate common to every Umwelt.//
[[/span]]

And this substrate has a beating heart. That's where we're going.
@@ @@
[[/collapsible]]
-----
[[div class="arancio"]]
[[collapsible show="▶ Step 4 | Information" hide="◀◀◀ Close Step Four"]]
[[/div]]
Reality is the most complex machine in existence.

Despite being so complex, its purpose is wide but relatively easy: to elaborate information. Every physical phenomenon, from a lightning to a dewdrop falling from a leaf, it's the result of an elaboration.

Reality, intended as the objective substrate at the base of everything, it's nothing but this: [[span style="color: gold"]]information[[/span]]. Everything else is perceived reality, subjective universes. [[span class="grigio"]]Bringers of information are the quantum fields.[[/span]]

You too, therefore, are information. [[span class="grigio"]]Hear me out now, because I have to do something a little difficult.[[/span]]

An electron is described by its quantum numbers, which represent the //state// of a particle. [[span class="grigio"]]//Spin// is the most famous quantum number.[[/span]]

The principle of [[span style="color: gold"]]indistinctness[[/span]] applies: if you swap two electrons with the same quantum numbers, then the resulting quantum field is unchanged, thus the information is the same. [[span class="grigio"]]Another example: take ten electrons from a stone. Change their quantum numbers in such a way that they are equal to ten of your electrons. Throw away your electrons and put the stone ones where yours were before. The result is that nothing has changed.[[/span]]

The previous principle applies to every subatomic particle, not just electrons. Therefore, if ideally I replaced every single particle of your body with a particle, taken from who knows where, but located in the same position and with the same quantum numbers, nothing would change.

[[span class="grigio"]]Actually... I just did that. As I said, the information hasn't changed. And the information includes your Umwelt, thus your memories and your perceptions. See? You're always yourself... I think. Yes, you see, my quantum transfer system is not //that// precise, some little error can happen every now and then... but you're still alive, am I right? Excellent, let's continue.[[/span]]

@@ @@
[[/collapsible]]
-----

[[collapsible show="▶ Step 5 | Life" hide="◀◀◀ Close Step Five"]]
Looking at life through a microscope, we can see cells.

[[span style="color: red"]]
= //A cell is a complex bio-machine, which executes millions of chemical reactions every second. But this is not what makes it alive.//
[[/span]]

No part of a cell is alive. The cell membrane is made of phospholipids, glycoproteins and other chemicals. The same goes for ribosomes, mitochondria, the Golgi apparatus, the nucleus, in short everything.

But you already know what a cell is for: to elaborate information. This machine (the cell) encodes the most important information into the DNA. [[span class="grigio"]]That is, genetic information.[[/span]]

Your neurons are like the CPU of a computer, only that they are made of various chemicals instead of being primarily based on silicon. [[span class="grigio"]]Your neurons even have a //clock// and communicate between each others varying the so-called //membrane potential//, an electric signal. A peak in that potential triggers the release of neurotransmitters, chemicals such as dopamine, which carry information between neurons.[[/span]]

After all, you're made by atoms. And atoms are not alive. Thus, where's life? Again, the answer is in the information.

The material substrate (cells, neurons, organs such as the brain) is just a [[span style="color: gold"]]support[[/span]] to the life. Life is in the information that your material substrate "supports". [[span class="grigio"]]In the same way that a platform (the body) supports a crystal vase (the life). If you remove the platform, the vase falls.[[/span]]

Everything you perceive as "life", therefore, is an illusion of your Umwelt. Even the feeling of being in your body.

[[span style="color: red"]]
= **Veil of Life**: //True life is outside of your Umwelt.//
[[/span]]

And this is the last veil to remove. When I will do it, the bubble where you always lived will burst.

@@ @@
[[/collapsible]]
-----
[[div class="viola"]]
[[collapsible show="▶ Step ▒ | Epilogue" hide="◀◀◀ Close Last Step"]]
[[/div]]

It's over.

The molecular degradation will start shortly.

[[span style="color: black"]]Wasn't that what you expected? If not, I'm sorry.

But that was my only option. It's the only possible way to free yourself permanently from your Umwelt.

In the first place, every single sensor of yours will be destroyed, you'll lose every chance of perceiving.
[[/span]]

Don't worry, you won't feel pain, [[span style="color: black"]]except when it will affect the brain[[/span]].

[[span style="color: black"]]In the second place, your neural activity will gradually cease. But that is only a superficial result.

At the deepest level, I'm cancelling the quantum information from every single particle that composes you. I'm eradicating the "memory" which the universe has of you.
[[/span]]

Keep calm.

[[span style="color: black"]]All the veils are falling.

You don't need to feel scared anymore.

You //can't// feel scared anymore.
[[/span]]

Everything will be alright.

[[span style="color: black"]]You asked me who I am, at the beginning.

I am what you human beings, confusingly, call "death".

Not physical death: that's just natural degradation.

I am the Messenger of the Quantum Death, Who cancels information from reality.

Simply put, I'm the medium between you and the Sublime One.

That's why your kind is scared by me.

In fact, they still think I am cruel.

But this is not true.

My mission is the noblest there is.

Bringing men to the Truth, that is the Sublime One.

Why am I doing this, you ask?

You'll soon find out... //in the other side//.
[[/span]]

[[span style="font-family: Dancing Script, cursive; font-size: 36px;"]]
[[include component:coltop show=Here... we arrived
|hide=Welcome to my world]]
[[/span]]

//Underwater... feeling of a force pushing upwards... emersion, puff of air...//

//Lifting from the water surface... sound of a sharp snap, feeling of pressure in the hips, ankles and shoulders...//

Can you still hear me?

//Stabilization at an equilibrium point...//

Good.

I told you a little lie.

Your information hasn't been cancelled yet.

No, this planet is not Earth.

Yes, it's always stormy here.

That enormous black sphere with the golden boarding, you say?

That is the Sublime One.

Yes, these columns of water come from the ocean below you.

How are you suspended in the air? Take a better look: you have a belt.

No, the belt keeps you //anchored// to the ocean floor.

It's a system of gravitational anchors.

//Water splash...//

Do you see these ropes raise from the ocean?

Yes, they're all like you.

No, relax: you can't die by starving nor by thirst. Not even by old age. And I even removed that need of sleeping. I removed those uncomfortable physiological restrictions.

Why are you so unnaturally calm, you ask? Do you remember me removing some of the emotions before you moved in?

You can think them, yes. But you can't feel them.

Why are you all here?

Obviously: to meet the Sublime One. But not yet.

I'm asking you to be patient, before your meeting with the Sublime One.

Yes, I first need all of you.

Every single human being.

Until then, you must wait here.

Do not worry: it won't take long. Some centuries, maybe.

[[span style="color: black"]]Oh, of course, you can hide me[[/span]]. [[span style="color: black"]]Contain me[[/span]]. [[span style="color: black"]]You can delay my noble mission[[/span]].

[[span style="color: black"]]But you can't stop me[[/span]].

